This paper is about few-shot relation classification, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the performance of state-of-the-art models and techniques, which suggests that it could be relevant to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), information retrieval (cs.IR), and neural networks (cs.NE).
